Object Oriented Programming

  Big Idea:
    - Encapsulate data that belongs together 
    - Encapsulate methods that operate on this data

    Static functions --> sqrt()

    static --> you can call it whenever




    Example: Bank Account

      Data: balance, name, PIN, interest rate, type, ID

      Methods: check balance, withdraw, deposit  (instance methods)

      instance variables --> store the data

      Needed for OOP:

          - Instance variables
          - constructors
          - instance methods


          "HEY STRING! WHAT ARE YOU IN LOWER CASE"

      Can reference classes from other scripts

      Ex:

      Account timAccount = new Account(123, 50.0)

      declare variables as `protected` so that the variables are "hidden"

      //constructor

      public Account(int myId, double initialBalance) {
        id = myId;
        balance = initialBalance;
      }


      public Account(int myId) {
        id = myId;
        balance = 0;
      }

      // instance methods

      public double getBalance(){
          return balance;
      }




      // Rectangles

      instance vars : (x,y), w, h
